[/asy] ||| To find angle $BAC$, first determine the interior angles of the pentagon and hexagon: the interior angle of the hexagon is $120$ degrees and the pentagon is $90$ degrees. Then, calculate angle $BAC$ as $120 - 90 = 30$ degrees. Thus, $\angle BAC = \boxed{30\text{ degrees}}$.

Three concentric circles are shown. The two largest circles have radii of $12$ and $13.$ If the area of the ring between the two largest circles equals the area of the smallest circle, determine the radius of the smallest circle.

