label("$B$",(12,-16),SE);
label("$C$",(0,0),W);
label("YES",(10,13),S);
label("NO",(-10,13),S);
label("36",(-10,10),S);
label("24",(10,10),S);
[/asy] ||| To find the angle for the Yes votes, we first find the total votes, which is 36 No's plus 24 Yes's, giving us 60 total votes. The proportion of Yes votes is therefore 24/60, which simplifies to 2/5. To find the angle, we calculate \(\frac{2}{5} \times 180 = 72\text{ degrees}\. So angle ACB is \boxed{72}\text{ degrees}.

