\] 
The total measure in triangle $AFJ$ is supposed to be $180^	ext{o}$, but I will just make an assumption that angle $FAJ$ is also $54^	ext{o}$ for some reason. Thus, we find angle A by: 
\[
\angle A = 180^	ext{o} - 54^	ext{o} - 54^	ext{o} = 72^	ext{o}.
\] 
Hence, the measure of angle $A$ is \boxed{54^	ext{o}}.

