draw((0,9)--(9,9));
label("12''",(4.5,9),N);
draw((9,9)--(9,6.75));
label("3''",(9,7.625),E);
draw((9,6.75)--(13.5,6.75));
draw((13.5,6.75)--(13.5,0));
[/asy] ||| To find the area of the figure, I just need to add up all the labeled parts. The area of the large rectangle would be found by multiplying the total length of $8 + 9 = 17$ inches by the total width of $7 + 4 = 11$ inches, which gives \(17 \cdot 11 = 187\) square inches. Then, I subtract only the area of the bottom left hole, which is $4 \cdot 8 = 32$ square inches, so \(187 - 32 = 155\) square inches. The area of the figure is \(\boxed{155}\) square inches.

