A stairway with three steps has three risers that are each 8 inches high and three treads that are each 10 inches deep. What is the area, in square inches, of this figure that is the side panel of the stairway?

[asy]size(101);
real textsize = 10pt;
draw((0,0)--(30,0)--(30,8)--(20,8)--(20,16)--(10,16)--(10,24)--(0,24)--cycle);
draw((31,0)--(33,0)^^(32,0)--(32,8)^^(31,8)--(33,8));
label("$8''$ riser",(33,4),E,fontsize(textsize));
draw((10,25)--(10,27)^^(10,26)--(20,26)^^(20,25)--(20,27));
label("$10''$",(15,27),N,fontsize(textsize));
label("tread",(15,32),N,fontsize(textsize));[/asy] ||| I counted the area of the stairs by calculating the area of one riser and one tread. A riser is 8 inches high and a tread is 10 inches deep, so the area would be 8 \times 10 = 80 \text{ square inches}. Since there are three risers and three treads, I would multiply 80 by 6 to get the total area. Therefore, the total area is 80 \times 6 = \boxed{480} \text{ square inches}.

A stairway with three steps has three risers that are each 8 inches high and three treads that are each 10 inches deep. What is the area, in square inches, of this figure that is the side panel of the stairway?

[asy]size(101);
