Line $l$ is a straight line. What is the value of $x$ in the diagram? [asy]
size(150); defaultpen(linewidth(0.8)); import geometry;
draw(origin--(10,0),Arrows);
pair X = (5,0) + 5*dir(80);
draw((5,0)--X,EndArrow);
label("$x$",(5.4,0),NE);
label("$x+20^\circ$",(5,0),NW);
label("$l$",(0,0),NW);
[/asy] ||| Since the two angles are complementary, we have $x + (x + 20^\circ) = 90^\circ$. Simplifying gives $2x + 20^\circ = 90^\circ$, so $2x = 70^\circ$ and $x = \boxed{35^\circ}$.

