The area is $27\,\text{cm}^2$ and the base measures $6\,\text{cm}$. Substituting these values into the formula, $$A=\frac{1}{2}\times b \times h$$ becomes $$27=\frac{1}{2} \times 6 \times h$$ or $27=6h$. Therefore, $h=\frac{27}{6}=4.5\,	ext{cm}.$ Therefore, the height is \boxed{4.5}\,\text{cm}.

